nly the B-Wing was more heavily armed. The fighter''s primary long-range weapon was its medium laser cannon which was mounted in a fully rotating dorsal turret. The weapon could only be fired from the turret''s gunnery chair; no fire control for the main weapon was included in the piloting cockpit; a design flaw meaning that, if the gunner was incapacitated, or indeed was not there, the primary weapon could not be used.','H-Wing1.jpg',NULL,'Source text CC-BY-SA 3.0 from http://d6holocron.com/wiki/H-Wing','["http://d6holocron.com/wiki/H-Wing"]',1828,51257);
